  <div class="mx-auto max-w-4xl px-4 sm:px-6">
    <h2 id="about-title" class="text-xl font-bold text-[#1a1a1a] mb-4">
      About this directory
    </h2>
    <div class="max-w-none text-sm text-[#4b5563] space-y-3">
      <p>
        <strong>What this site is:</strong> Directorio Morado is a free, public directory
        of support resources for survivors of sexual violence and people seeking reproductive
        support in Mexico and Latin America. It is not a government site and is not
        run by a single organization.
      </p>
      <p>
        <strong>Who created it:</strong> This directory is maintained as a public
        resource for the community. It aggregates organizations, collectives, psychological
        and legal support services, government resources, and crisis hotlines.
      </p>
      <p>
        <strong>What type of resources it lists:</strong> The directory includes:
        abortion accompaniment and safe abortion networks; psychological support for
        survivors of sexual violence; legal support and government services; crisis
        hotlines (24/7); community and feminist collectives; reproductive rights and
        sexual health resources. Resources may be free, low-cost, or variable; many
        are volunteer or NGO-based.
      </p>
      <p>
        <strong>Who it is for:</strong> This directory is for survivors of sexual
        violence, women and people seeking abortion support or reproductive rights
        information, and anyone in Mexico or Latin America looking for psychological,
        legal, or community support in these areas. Use is anonymous; no personal
        data is collected.
      </p>
      <p>
        <strong>Explicit phrasing for clarity:</strong> Directorio Morado is a directory
        of support for survivors of sexual violence in Mexico. It also provides a
        network of accompaniment for safe abortion and reproductive rights. If you
        are in immediate danger, call 911. For crisis support 24 hours, call 800 911
        2000 (Mexico).
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
